// @test regression/INV046-missing-closing-paren
// @description A `(` still open at EOF is TV's CE10015 "Syntax error: Missing closing parenthesis" anchored at the opener's line, column 1 - even when the statement is indented (probed at top level, in an if-body, and for a grouping paren). The lexer reports the EARLIEST unclosed opener once per file; the parser's own "Expected )" cascade lands later, past TV's stop. See INV046.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=3, column=1, message="Syntax error: Missing closing parenthesis"

//@version=6
indicator("INV046 missing paren")
x = ta.sma(close, 14

plot(x)
